  </div>

  <!-- About -->
  <div class="py-5" id="about">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="p-3 pb-md-4 mx-auto text-center">
        <h2 class="pb-2 border-bottom">My Story</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-10 order-md-2">
          <h2 class="fw-normal lh-1 featurette-heading">Hi, I'm Ruth, 
            <span>founder of True Story Resumes</span>
          </h2>
          <p>
            I have a Master's degree in Engineering, Economics, and Management, and have spent over a decade in a variety of roles in different industries. I first started writing resumes professionally during Covid-19, when I found myself confined to my small apartment with too much time to kill. <br><br>
            In 2023, I attended a coding bootcamp and met lots of motivated professionals from teachers to visual artists dentists, and veterinarians, all hoping to make a career switch into tech. Unfortunately, we graduated amidst massive layoffs in the tech industry and found ourselves fighting a losing resume battle against many more experienced developers. After 3 months of rejections, I was a wreck. I didn't know the person in my resume and was convinced that I had no useful professional skills. <br><br>
            Then I met a wonderful recruiter and career coach. She listened to me talk through my career history, pointing out my strengths, and reassuring me that my varied experiences were an asset to the right employer. This gave me a renewed confidence in my job search. <br><br>
            Around the same time, I met several other bootcamp graduates in the same situation. Reviewing their resumes, I noticed they looked almost identical! All downplayed their previous experiences, per bootcamps' career services advice, unintentionally resulting in bland, cookie cutter resumes. Remembering how cathartic it had been to have my career viewed in its entirety, I made it my mission to bring back the whole person into the resumes of career switchers. <br><br>
            It can be challenging to craft a clear narrative when switching careers, but I believe showcasing your unique journey is crucial. While I can't guarantee job interviews, I promise to deliver a resume that authentically demonstrates your strengths and experiences, so that you have compelling talking points for memorable conversations with potential hiring managers. I look forward to hearing your story! <br><br>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-2 order-md-1">
          <img src="images/ruth_photo.jpg" width=100% class="rounded-circle object-fit-contain" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

<%- include("partials/footer.ejs") %>